  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6585.86 sitting below the 6595 GEX flip in PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip as hedging flows, providing downside support. The massive +69.8B gamma wall at 6600 creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts, while the -10.9B negative gamma pocket at 6570 represents the key support level where dealer buying accelerates. The wall_break and gex_surge events combined with the -36% GEX drop signal recent option flows have restructured the hedging landscape, but the dense positive gamma cluster from 6590-6610 should contain volatility and promote mean reversion back toward 6595-6600.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to grind higher toward 6600 but face heavy resistance there.",
